This paper discusses the wireless technologies used in the Internet of Things (IoT), which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). It also evaluates the capabilities and behaviors of these technologies, which involves information theory (cs.IT), security (cs.CR), and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for a multifaceted technology approach, which could also fall under machine learning (cs.MA) as it involves developing intelligent systems.
